=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Interpreter_ex9 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 201 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 201.1586
  harmonic_decay_rate: -16.9000
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5863
  pitch_clarity: 49.7275
  inharmonicity: 0.0029
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.7913
  resonance_freq: 193.7988

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Interpreter Example 9
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Interpreter.html
// Tags: Interpreter, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 9 ---
// silly but simple: understand a Saw for every SinOsc
this.preProcessor = { |code| code.replace("SinOsc", "Saw") };

{ SinOsc.ar(200) * 0.1 }.play;

preProcessor = nil; // reset to nil.
